;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6272a4&#34;&gt;/* some scoped CSS go in here */&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff79c6&#34;&gt;style&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is probably a reflection of how much time I&amp;rsquo;ve spent in Vue.js recently, but it&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;conceptually&lt;/em&gt; what I&amp;rsquo;m imagining is required to build something as a Web Component.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
